-- Aramco’s Al-Othman Named Head of Saudi Investment Authority
-- B y   W a e l   M a h d i
-- 2012-05-18T14:58:24Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-18/aramco-s-al-othman-named-head-of-saudi-investment-authority.html
Abdullatif A al-Othman, a former
executive with Saudi Arabian Oil Co., was appointed head of the
 Saudi Arabian General Investment Authority  by  King Abdullah ,
according to a royal decree carried today by the official Saudi
Press Agency.  Al-Othman served as senior vice president, Engineering and
Project Management for  Saudi Aramco  before joining the
investment authority, a Riyadh-based spokesman for the authority
confirmed in a text message.  Al-Othman, who holds a masters degree in business
administration from the Massachusetts Institute of Technology,
joined Saudi Aramco in March 1981 as an engineer in Engineering
and Project Management. He worked in several technical and
administrative positions including senior vice president of
finance, according Saudi Aramco’s website.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Wael Mahdi in Khobar at   wmahdi@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Stephen Voss at   sev@bloomberg.net  